title: Smooth yogurt with just right thickness and tartness
review: This is my favorite low-fat yogurt!It is not too thick or too thin, and smooth with the right amount of tartness.I used to love whole milk yogurt but am trying to cut down on the fat.Tried lots of different Greek yogurts and some were too thick and hard to stir in fruits and nuts.Others were too tart or watery.Perfect!

title: Oh darling, you've changed ....
review: This used to be the best. Past few months now it's been thin. Like on the verge of runny. I'm not sure if the ingredients changed or the process changed but.... either way I'm out. So now I'm searching for a good low fat plain yogurt for breakfast - def appreciate any suggestions ;-) Meanwhile back to low-fat cottage cheese until a suitable replacement can be found.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on March 6, 2019
name: mushroombaby
title: Not that tart compared to other non-fat greek yogurt
review: I eat greek yogurt everyday and have tried numerious brands of greek yogurt. I prefer low in fat content but cannot eat something very tart. This one is not that tart compared to most non-fat greek yogurt. Actually, it tastes more like low-fat. But it is even more creamy than low fat greek yogurt of other brands. Love it!

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 20, 2021
name: masterfufu
title: Consistent breakfast staple for the past 4 years
review: On the more expensive side, but still great value for the money. Simple ingredient list gives me peace of mind, and as a fitness enthusiast, this yogurt has the best sugar-protein ratio on the market while still being delicious. Aside from being a breakfast staple, it’s also a great ingredient for many of my baking projects. I honestly wouldn’t know what I’d substitute this with, so please keep making this product!
